        start_zone = 'Windurst Woods',
        start_pos = 'K-7',
        description = 'Go to Mhaura and meet Koh Lenbalalako. It is said that she knows the whereabouts of the sinner\'s daughter.',
        reward = 'Hunter\'s Beret',
        fame = 'Windurst',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = 'none',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'Sin Hunting'},
        next = {
            'Unbridled Passion',
            'Borghertz\'s Chasing Hands',
        },
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Old Earring', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Talk to Perih Vashai in Windurst Woods (K-7) and she will tell you to go to Mhaura and visit the Blacksmiths\' guild.\n2. In Mhaura head to (F-9) to speak with Koh Lenbalalako. Speak with her twice to receive a cutscene where she will tell you to head to Eldieme Necropolis.\n   - Koh is found inside the Blacksmith Guild.\n3. Enter Eldieme Necropolis through Batallia Downs at (I-10) and get another cutscene with the Mithran Tracker telling you to examine the stone monuments in search of the name of the sinner\'s daughter.\n   - You do not need to be on ranger for this part of the quest.\n   - The Eldieme Necropolis Survival Guide will put you at the correct entrance, but will not activate the cutscene. You must zone out and back in.\n4. Head to (G-9) and examine the Gravestone to trigger another cutscene with the Mithra Tracker.\n   - If you have the Magicked astrolabe you can get here solo.\n5. After the cutscene head back to Windurst Woods and speak with Perih Vashai again.\n6. You will get another cutscene with the Mithran Tracker, where you are told by Perih Vashai to head to Castle Oztroja to search a pool for an Old Earring.\n7. The next step in Castle Oztroja requires Scavenge, so set your job or subjob accordingly.\n   - Once in Castle Oztroja head to (I-8) on the first map, and hit the correct handle to go through the brass door.\n   - On the second map, head to (I-10) to get the 4 switch password for the game day. Then head to the brass door at (G-8) and enter the 4 switch combination.\n     - You can also just play around with it until it opens rather than go to the room at (I-10).\n   - Head up the stairs to the third map where you\'ll find a pool of water with leeches in it at (H-9).\n   - Use the job ability Scavenge until you get the Old Earring.\n     - This may take more than one attempt. You can come as a high level job and sub Ranger for Scavenge, as you can obtain the earring this way.\n8. Take the Old Earring and trade it to Perih Vashai for a cutscene and the Hunter\'s Beret.',
        notes = nil,
    },
