    ['Hat in Hand'] = {
        id = 0,
        start_npc = 'Baren-Moren',
        start_zone = 'Windurst Waters',
        start_pos = 'H-7',
        description = 'Advertise Baren-Moren\'s latest\ncreation by chatting with the local\ninhabitants of Windurst Waters.\nHe\'ll pay you according to the\nnumber of townsfolk you speak to.\nBut, you are not to leave Windurst\nWaters before completing the task.',
        reward = '50-200 gil and/or Windshear Hat .',
        fame = 'Windurst',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'Yes',
        previous = nil,
        next = {'A Feather in One\'s Cap'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Baren-Moren (H-7) to begin the quest and get the New model hat.\n2. Mandatory NPCs you need to show the hat to:\n   - Bondada  inside the hat shop.\n   - Honoi-Gomoi in the upper portion of Gingerberry Grove (E-7) (South Map).\n     - Located in the residence to the right, however, you must go around the back of the house and up the stairs in order to meet him.\n   - Kenapa-Keppa inside the most southern door of the Rhinostery (South Map).\n   - Clais on the wooden bridge leading to the Rarab\'s Tail Hostelery / Timbre Timbers Tavern G-10 (North Map).\n   - Kyume-Romeh in the Timbre Timbers Tavern (F-10) (North Map).\n   - Tosuka-Porika in the east Optistery building (G-8) (North Map).\n   - Pechiru-Mashiru in the east Aurastery building (L-6) (North Map).\n   - Machitata near the Mog House (L-11) (North Map).\n3. The more NPCs you talk to, the greater your final reward, up to a maximum of 200 gil and a Windshear Hat.\n   - <20 NPCs: You will not get credit or complete the quest\n   - 20~29 NPCs: 50 gil, no hat.\n   - 30~39 NPCs: 120 gil, no hat.\n   - 40~79 NPCs: 150 gil and a Windshear Hat.\n   - 80+ NPCS: 200 gil and a Windshear Hat.\n4. After you have shown the hat to the eight mandatory NPCs and 12 additional NPCs (i.e. 20 total), speak to Baren-Moren again to hang-up the hat which completes the quest.\n5. Zoning will reset any NPC spoken to before turning the hat in.',
        notes = nil,
    },
